profile_positions.description:
Main responsabilities : 

- Taught according to the educational needs, abilities, and achievement of the individual students and groups of students;
- Assigned work, corrected and marked work carried out by my students;
- Assessed, recorded, and reported on the development, progress, attainment, and behavior of my students;
- Provided and contributed to oral and written assessments, reports, and references relating to individual students or groups of students;
- Maintained good order and discipline amongst my students;
- Provided guidance and advice to students on educational and social matters and on their further education and future careers, providing information on sources of more expert advice;
- Promoted the general progress and well-being of individual students, which was one of the goals of the center. 

Accomplishments : 

- My main accomplishment was my participation in the "Robotics program" training that aimed to send students abroad to participate in international contests, in Malaysia or Dubai, for example. 
- My close relationship with all the administrational staff allowed me to know about the plans, the budgets, and the projects of the company. My manager, despite my young age, 18 at that time, had put particular trust in me, and often asked me for initiatives, advice, and some particular works that were, polyvalent, more related to project coordinating than teaching.
